{"tid":2262104,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"美國政府無法制裁親中社交媒體 民主黨議員力挺媒體大亨","createTime":"2020-10-28T23:13:29.000Z","updateTime":"2020-10-28T23:30:42.000Z","uid":337052,"like":2,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":4,"replies":[{"pid":"c300279ad7bf0953e6a14b421f2ac2b83fe669a6","tid":2262104,"uid":337052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-28T23:13:29.000Z","msg":"<strong><span class=\"x-large\">美參院辦聽證會拷問科技巨頭CEO 議員忙互批</span></strong><br />\n最新更新：2020/10/29 05:23<br />\n<br />\n（中央社華盛頓28日綜合外電報導）<span class=\"red\">美國參議院今天就改革一項網路法令，以及對科技公司審查內容的方式究責一事召開聽證會，但場面很快淪為政治混戰。議員緊咬推特、谷歌、臉書等科技企業，同時也相互攻訐。</span><br />\n<br />\n路透社報導，美國「通訊端正法」（Communications Decency Act）第230條保護科技公司免於為用戶張貼的內容負責，同時卻允許這些企業能形塑政治論述。對於如何依法讓大企業負起責任，議員們看法分歧。<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">推特（Twitter）執行長（CEO）杜錫（Jack Dorsey）、臉書（Facebook）執行長祖克柏（Mark Zuckerberg）、Alphabet旗下谷歌公司（Google）執行長佩吉（Larry Page）表示，通訊端正法第230條對於網路言論自由而言至關重要。</span><br />\n<br />\n聽證會開始約一小時後，場面演變成兩黨參議員激烈交鋒。<br />\n<br />\n杜錫說推特對選舉沒有影響力，遭共和黨籍聯邦參議員克魯茲（Ted Cruz）抨擊。克魯茲說：「杜錫先生，到底是誰選你出來，讓你掌管媒體被允許報導、以及美國人民可以聽見的內容？」<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">民主黨籍聯邦參議員夏茨（Brian Schatz）則表示自己沒有任何問題，還形容這場聽證會是「胡鬧」。</span>夏茨表示：「這是在霸凌（CEO們），是為了選舉目的。」<br />\n<br />\n參議院商務委員會民主黨籍首席議員肯特威爾（Maria Cantwell）也說，如果聽證會是在11月3日大選後、在明年1月舉行會更好。國會今年鮮有機會處理這項法律。<br />\n<br />\n總統川普指控科技巨擘箝制保守派的聲音，聽證會進行期間，共和黨籍議員上傳一系列推文，川普也推文說：「廢除第230條！」（譯者：楊昭彥）1091029<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://project.cna.com.tw/20201005-USelection/202010290014\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fproject.cna.com.tw%2F20201005-USelection%2F202010290014&d=2u41qa%2Bce9Gslgrzp%2F5KivsPRfgRtgRFNgQ5kFpanIU%3D&h=0bdc30a1\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://project.cna.com.tw/20201005-USelection/202010290014</a>"},{"pid":"95cd76821fbae3451a6e3186de069d86669966de","tid":2262104,"uid":337052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-28T23:15:45.000Z","msg":"Facebook, Twitter and Google face questions from US senators<br />\n<img src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/747C/production/_115102892_techtrio.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F800%2Fcpsprodpb%2F747C%2Fproduction%2F_115102892_techtrio.jpg&h=4785a006&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-54721023\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-54721023&d=2u41qa%2Bce9Gslgrzp%2F5KivsPRfgRtgRFNgQ5kFpanIU%3D&h=f8d207a8\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-54721023&h=486202af\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-54721023</a>"},{"pid":"db22f49d91bb282b7df1af4c08aa1ec16612ad11","tid":2262104,"uid":337052,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-28T23:17:55.000Z","msg":"Jack Dorsey says the New York Post Twitter account will remain locked until it deletes the original tweet featuring its Hunter Biden story<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/jack-dorsey-ny-post-remains-locked-out-twitter-hunter-biden-2020-10\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-dorsey-ny-post-remains-locked-out-twitter-hunter-biden-2020-10&d=2u41qa%2Bce9Gslgrzp%2F5KivsPRfgRtgRFNgQ5kFpanIU%3D&h=f660a6d8\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.businessinsider.com/jack-dorsey-ny-post-remains-locked-out-twitter-hunter-biden-2020-10</a>"},{"pid":"b83917b850dae1cf906c94a1623870020e70946a","tid":2262104,"uid":28279,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-28T23:25:18.000Z","msg":"而家有政治審查都叫言論自由<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />咁中國咪最自由既國家"},{"pid":"31ba36058991d49f6a3274f053f2f67c1e4f0b4b","tid":2262104,"uid":155095,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"b83917b850dae1cf906c94a1623870020e70946a","tid":2262104,"uid":28279,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-28T23:25:18.000Z","msg":"而家有政治審查都叫言論自由<img src=\"